h3cConfig.name: h3cConfig

revisions.description: The initial revision of this MIB module.

h3cConfig.contactinfo: Platform Team Hangzhou H3C Tech. Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China http://www.h3c.com Zip:100085
h3cConfig.description: This MIB contains objects to manage the system configuration. It contains the model used to represent configuration data that exists elsewhere in the system and in peripheral devices. There are no constraints on this MIB.

ConfigOperationType.name: ConfigOperationType
ConfigOperationType.description: Specify operation types on configuration. Currently, following types of operation are provided: running2Startup(1): Update the saved configuration (startup) file used currently with the current configuration running in the system. This operation is equivalent to the [save] command from command line. If current startup configuration file does not exist, then the default startup configuration file is created to save the data and this becomes the current startup configuration file. startup2Running(2): Update the current configuration running in the system with the saved configuration (startup) file used currently. The commands in the file are executed as if they had been entered via the command line. If the current startup configuration file does not exist, the operation will fail with the error opFileOpenError(13). running2Net(3): Send the current configuration running in the system to the network using the specified file transfer protocol. net2Running(4): Update the current configuration running in the system with a remote file from the network using the specified file transfer protocol. The commands in the file are executed as if they had been entered via the command line. net2Startup(5): Download a remote file to the local system using the specified file transfer protocol and replace the saved configuration (startup) file used currently. If current startup configurationfile does not exist, the default startup configuration file is created to save the data and this becomes the current startup configuration file. startup2Net(6): Send the saved configuration (startup) file used currently to the network using the specified file transfer protocol. If the current startup configuration file does not exist, the operation will fail with the error opFileOpenError(13).

ConfigOperationStateType.name: ConfigOperationStateType
ConfigOperationStateType.description: The status of the specified operation. opInProgress : Specified operation is active. opOperationSuccess : Specified operation is supported and completed successfully. opInvalidOperation : Command invalid or command/protocol/device combination unsupported. opInvalidProtocol : Invalid protocol specified. opInvalidSourceName : Invalid source file name specified. opInvalidDestName : Invalid target name specified. opInvalidServerAddress : Invalid server address specified. opDeviceBusy : Specified device is in use and locked by another process. opDeviceOpenError : Invalid device name. opDeviceError : Device read, write or erase error. opDeviceNotProgrammable : Device is read-only but a write or erase operation was specified. opDeviceFull : Device is filled to capacity. opFileOpenError : Invalid file name; file not found in partition. opFileTransferError : File transfer was unsuccessful; network failure. opFileChecksumError : File checksum in Flash failed. opNoMemory : System running low on memory. opAuthFail: Invalid user name or password. opTimeOut : File transfer was timeout. opUnknownFailure : Failure unknown. opInvalidConfigFile: Invalid configration file. opSlaveFull : Operation is fail for the slave don't have enough space. opCopyToSlaveFailure : Operation is fail when copy file to the slave.

h3cCfgRunModifiedLast.name: h3cCfgRunModifiedLast
h3cCfgRunModifiedLast.description: The object records the value of sysUpTime when the current configuration running in the system was last modified. The value will be changed immediately after system detects the current configuration has been changed.

h3cCfgRunSavedLast.name: h3cCfgRunSavedLast
h3cCfgRunSavedLast.description: The object records the value of sysUpTime when the current configuration running in the system was last saved. If the value of the object is smaller than h3cCfgRunModifiedLast, the current configuration has been modified but not saved.

h3cCfgStartModifiedLast.name: h3cCfgStartModifiedLast
h3cCfgStartModifiedLast.description: The object records the value of sysUpTime when the saved configuration used currently was last modified. It may have been modified by a save of the current configuration running in the system or other methods such as copy.

h3cCfgLogLimitedEntries.name: h3cCfgLogLimitedEntries
h3cCfgLogLimitedEntries.description: The object shows the maximum number of rows in h3cCfgLogTable. The value supported by the system is 10.

h3cCfgLogDeletedEntries.name: h3cCfgLogDeletedEntries
h3cCfgLogDeletedEntries.description: The total number of rows deleted from h3cCfgLogTable.

h3cCfgLogWantBackup.name: h3cCfgLogWantBackup
h3cCfgLogWantBackup.description: Decide whether to backup the value of objects about h3cCfgLog.

h3cCfgLogTable.name: h3cCfgLogTable
h3cCfgLogTable.description: Table for logging configuration operation in device.

h3cCfgLogIndex.name: h3cCfgLogIndex
h3cCfgLogIndex.description: Index of the table beginning from 1.

h3cCfgLogTime.name: h3cCfgLogTime
h3cCfgLogTime.description: Specify the sysUpTime when the config log was generated.

h3cCfgLogSrcCmd.name: h3cCfgLogSrcCmd
h3cCfgLogSrcCmd.description: Specify the source command which brought the log. Currently we provide the types of source: 1.cmdLine(1):configure log instigated by command line. 2.snmp(2):configure log instigated by snmp. 3.other(3):configure log instigated by other source unknown.

h3cCfgLogSrcData.name: h3cCfgLogSrcData
h3cCfgLogSrcData.description: The source of the configuration data event. erase erasing destination runningData operational data alive commandSource the command source itself startupData what the system will use next reboot local local NVRAM or flash netFtp FTP network transfer hotPlugging board is inserted or pulled out on line

h3cCfgLogDesData.name: h3cCfgLogDesData
h3cCfgLogDesData.description: The destination for the configuration data event. unknown unknown runningData operational data alive commandSource the command source itself startupData what the system will use next reboot local local NVRAM or flash netFtp FTP network transfer hotPlugging board is inserted or pulled out on line

h3cCfgLogTerminalType.name: h3cCfgLogTerminalType
h3cCfgLogTerminalType.description: Specifies the terminal type. If h3cCfgLogSrcCmd is not 'cmdLine', use 'notApplicable'. The value list: notApplicable(1): no meaning at this time. unknown(2): unknown terminal type. console(3): console interface. terminal(4): generic terminal. virtual(5): virtual terminal such as telnet. auxiliary(6): auxiliary interface.

h3cCfgLogTerminalUser.name: h3cCfgLogTerminalUser
h3cCfgLogTerminalUser.description: The name of logging user which is available when h3cCfgLogSrcCmd is 'cmdLine'. Other, a zero length string.

h3cCfgLogTerminalNum.name: h3cCfgLogTerminalNum
h3cCfgLogTerminalNum.description: Specifies the terminal number. If h3cCfgLogSrcCmd is not 'cmdLine', use '-1'

h3cCfgLogTerminalLocation.name: h3cCfgLogTerminalLocation
h3cCfgLogTerminalLocation.description: The location of logging user which is available when h3cCfgLogSrcCmd is 'cmdLine'. Other, a zero length string.

h3cCfgLogCmdSrcAddress.name: h3cCfgLogCmdSrcAddress
h3cCfgLogCmdSrcAddress.description: The address from which a request comes when the value of h3cCfgLogSrcCmd is 'snmp(2)'. The ip address of the remote system connected when the value of h3cCfgLogTerminalType is 'virtual'. Other, the value of 0.0.0.0. This object is replaced by for it only support IPv4.

h3cCfgLogVirHost.name: h3cCfgLogVirHost
h3cCfgLogVirHost.description: The host name of remote system connected if h3cCfgLogTerminalType has the value of 'virtual'. Other, a zero length string.

h3cCfgLogUserName.name: h3cCfgLogUserName
h3cCfgLogUserName.description: The user name used when h3cCfgLogSrcData or h3cCfgLogDesData has the value of 'netFtp'. Other, a zero length string.

h3cCfgLogServerAddress.name: h3cCfgLogServerAddress
h3cCfgLogServerAddress.description: The remote server address when h3cCfgLogSrcData or h3cCfgLogDesData has the value of 'netFtp'. Other, a value of 0.0.0.0. This object is replaced by for it only support IPv4.

h3cCfgLogFile.name: h3cCfgLogFile
h3cCfgLogFile.description: The current configuration file name when h3cCfgLogSrcData has the value of 'netFtp',and h3cCfgLogDesData has the value of 'startupData'. Other, a zero length string.

h3cCfgLogCmdSrcAddrType.name: h3cCfgLogCmdSrcAddrType
h3cCfgLogCmdSrcAddrType.description: The type of IP address for the h3cCfgLogCmdSrcAddrRev.

h3cCfgLogCmdSrcAddrRev.name: h3cCfgLogCmdSrcAddrRev
h3cCfgLogCmdSrcAddrRev.description: The address from which a request comes when the value of h3cCfgLogSrcCmd is 'snmp(2)'. The ip address of the remote system connected when the value of h3cCfgLogTerminalType is 'virtual'. Other, the value of 0.0.0.0.

h3cCfgLogCmdSrcAddrVPNName.name: h3cCfgLogCmdSrcAddrVPNName
h3cCfgLogCmdSrcAddrVPNName.description: The VPN instance of this operation uses.

h3cCfgLogServerAddrType.name: h3cCfgLogServerAddrType
h3cCfgLogServerAddrType.description: The type of IP address for the h3cCfgLogServerAddrRev.

h3cCfgLogServerAddrRev.name: h3cCfgLogServerAddrRev
h3cCfgLogServerAddrRev.description: The remote server address when h3cCfgLogSrcData or h3cCfgLogDesData has the value of 'netFtp'. Other, a value of 0.0.0.0.

h3cCfgLogServerAddrVPNName.name: h3cCfgLogServerAddrVPNName
h3cCfgLogServerAddrVPNName.description: The VPN instance of this operation uses.

h3cCfgOperateGlobalEntryLimit.name: h3cCfgOperateGlobalEntryLimit
h3cCfgOperateGlobalEntryLimit.description: The maximum number of copy entries that may be held in h3cCfgOperateTable. A particular setting does not guarantee that much data can be held.

h3cCfgOperateEntryAgeOutTime.name: h3cCfgOperateEntryAgeOutTime
h3cCfgOperateEntryAgeOutTime.description: The number of minutes an unactive h3cCfgOperateEntry SHOULD be kept in the h3cCfgOperateTable before it is active. The object is a fator taken account of when it needs delete some rows make room in h3cCfgOperateTable.

h3cCfgOperateResultGlobalEntryLimit.name: h3cCfgOperateResultGlobalEntryLimit
h3cCfgOperateResultGlobalEntryLimit.description: The maximum number of copy entries that may be held in h3cCfgOperateResultTable. A particular setting does not guarantee that much data can be held.

h3cCfgOperateIndex.name: h3cCfgOperateIndex
h3cCfgOperateIndex.description: The unique index value of a row in this table.

h3cCfgOperateType.name: h3cCfgOperateType
h3cCfgOperateType.description: Specify the type of operation on configuration.

h3cCfgOperateProtocol.name: h3cCfgOperateProtocol
h3cCfgOperateProtocol.description: If the value of h3cCfgOperateType is running2Net,net2Running,net2Startup or startup2net, this node specify the protocol to be used for file transfer . The default protocol is ftp if no protocol is specified. And for other value of h3cCfgOperateType , this object may be ignored by the implementation. when clusterftp or clustertftp is selected, the h3cCfgOperateServerAddress needn't be set, the server address can be acquired automatically, the value of h3cCfgOperateServerAddress is uncertain during operation. both member switch and commander switch can use them if they support HGMP v2.

h3cCfgOperateFileName.name: h3cCfgOperateFileName
h3cCfgOperateFileName.description: When the object of h3cCfgOperateType has the value of net2Startup, net2running or running2Net,the value must be specified. The file name may include the path if applicable. If the value of h3cCfgOperateType is net2Startup or net2running, this node specify the source file name of transfers.If the value of h3cCfgOperateType is running2Net , this node specify the destination file name of transfers. When h3cCfgOperateType has the value of startup2net,the object may not be created instead of using the file name of startup configuration file.

h3cCfgOperateServerAddress.name: h3cCfgOperateServerAddress
h3cCfgOperateServerAddress.description: When the operation type is running2Net,net2Running,net2Startup or startup2net , the ip address of the ftp/tftp server from/to which to download/upload must be specified. Values of 0.0.0.0 or FF.FF.FF.FF are not permitted. This object is replaced by h3cFlhOperSrvAddr for it only support IPv4.

h3cCfgOperateUserName.name: h3cCfgOperateUserName
h3cCfgOperateUserName.description: When the operation type is running2Net,net2Running,net2Startup or startup2net , the user name for the ftp server from/to which to download/upload should be specified. The object must be created if h3cCfgOperateProtocol has the value of ftp.

h3cCfgOperateUserPassword.name: h3cCfgOperateUserPassword
h3cCfgOperateUserPassword.description: When the operation type is running2Net,net2Running,net2Startup or startup2net , the user password for the ftp server from/to which to download/upload should be specified. The object must be created if h3cCfgOperateProtocol has the value of ftp.

h3cCfgOperateEndNotificationSwitch.name: h3cCfgOperateEndNotificationSwitch
h3cCfgOperateEndNotificationSwitch.description: Specifies whether or not a notification should be issued on the completion of the operation.

h3cCfgOperateRowStatus.name: h3cCfgOperateRowStatus
h3cCfgOperateRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry. When the status is active all the object's value in the entry is not allowed to modified.

h3cCfgOperateServerPort.name: h3cCfgOperateServerPort
h3cCfgOperateServerPort.description: When the operation type is running2Net, net2Running, net2Startup or startup2Net, this node is used for specifying the remote port number. If the value is 0 or not specified, the known port number will be used.

h3cCfgOperateSrvAddrType.name: h3cCfgOperateSrvAddrType
h3cCfgOperateSrvAddrType.description: The type of IP address for h3cCfgOperateSrvAddrRev.

h3cCfgOperateSrvAddrRev.name: h3cCfgOperateSrvAddrRev
h3cCfgOperateSrvAddrRev.description: When the operation type is running2Net,net2Running,net2Startup or startup2net , the ip address of the ftp/tftp server from/to which to download/upload must be specified.

h3cCfgOperateSrvVPNName.name: h3cCfgOperateSrvVPNName
h3cCfgOperateSrvVPNName.description: The VPN instance of this operation uses.

h3cCfgOperateResultTable.name: h3cCfgOperateResultTable
h3cCfgOperateResultTable.description: A table of config-operation requests result.

h3cCfgOperateResultEntry.name: h3cCfgOperateResultEntry
h3cCfgOperateResultEntry.description: The result entries of configuration operation requests.

h3cCfgOperateResultIndex.name: h3cCfgOperateResultIndex
h3cCfgOperateResultIndex.description: The index of Table, which is an incremental integer. The maximum value of the node is 2147483647. The agent should wrap the value to 1 and flush all the existing entries when the maximum value is reached.

h3cCfgOperateResultOptIndex.name: h3cCfgOperateResultOptIndex
h3cCfgOperateResultOptIndex.description: The operation index in the h3cCfgOperateTable.

h3cCfgOperateResultOpType.name: h3cCfgOperateResultOpType
h3cCfgOperateResultOpType.description: The operation type in the h3cCfgOperateTable.

h3cCfgOperateState.name: h3cCfgOperateState
h3cCfgOperateState.description: The operation state type in the h3cCfgOperateTable.

h3cCfgOperateTime.name: h3cCfgOperateTime
h3cCfgOperateTime.description: Record the time taken for the operation. This object will be like a stopwatch, starting when the operation starts, and stopping when the operation completes.

h3cCfgOperateEndTime.name: h3cCfgOperateEndTime
h3cCfgOperateEndTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when the configuration operation is finished.

h3cCfgOperFailReason.name: h3cCfgOperFailReason
h3cCfgOperFailReason.description: The failure reasons of configuration operation.

h3cCfgExecuteOperateResultEntryLimit.name: h3cCfgExecuteOperateResultEntryLimit
h3cCfgExecuteOperateResultEntryLimit.description: The maximum number of ConfigOperationType entries that may be held in h3cCfgExecuteResultTable. A particular setting does not guarantee that much data can be held.

h3cCfgExecuteResultTable.name: h3cCfgExecuteResultTable
h3cCfgExecuteResultTable.description: A table of configuration execute result.

h3cCfgExecuteResultEntry.name: h3cCfgExecuteResultEntry
h3cCfgExecuteResultEntry.description: The result entries of configuration execute operation.

h3cCfgExecuteResultIndex.name: h3cCfgExecuteResultIndex
h3cCfgExecuteResultIndex.description: The index of Table, which is an incremental integer. The maximum value of the node is 2147483647. The agent should wrap the value to 1 and flush all the existing entries when the maximum value is reached.

h3cCfgExecuteResultOptIndex.name: h3cCfgExecuteResultOptIndex
h3cCfgExecuteResultOptIndex.description: The configuration execute operation index in the h3cCfgExecuteResultTable.

h3cCfgExecuteResultOpType.name: h3cCfgExecuteResultOpType
h3cCfgExecuteResultOpType.description: The operation type in the h3cCfgExecuteResultTable.

h3cCfgExecuteState.name: h3cCfgExecuteState
h3cCfgExecuteState.description: Record the status of the specified operation.

h3cCfgExecuteTime.name: h3cCfgExecuteTime
h3cCfgExecuteTime.description: Record the time of the execution starts.

h3cCfgExecuteEndTime.name: h3cCfgExecuteEndTime
h3cCfgExecuteEndTime.description: Record the time of the execution is finished.

h3cCfgManEventlog.name: h3cCfgManEventlog
h3cCfgManEventlog.description: The object calculates the checksum on the current config per 10 minutes and even if it is different from the saved config but if a trap has been sent with the same checksum then don't send again until the checksum is different.

h3cCfgOperateCompletion.name: h3cCfgOperateCompletion
h3cCfgOperateCompletion.description: When create h3cCfgOperateTable successfully, a notification may be generated.

h3cCfgInvalidConfigFile.name: h3cCfgInvalidConfigFile
h3cCfgInvalidConfigFile.description: When the configuration file is invalid, this notification will be generated.

h3cConfigManCompliance.name: h3cConfigManCompliance
h3cConfigManCompliance.description: The statement of compliance for those implementing the Huawei 3Com ConfigMan MIB.

h3cCfgManLogGroup.name: h3cCfgManLogGroup
h3cCfgManLogGroup.description: A collection of objects configuration log group.
